You are to build a full cross-platform AI orchestration system consisting of:

1. Desktop application (Tauri)
2. Mobile application (React Native / Expo)
3. Backend server (Debian Linux)
4. Worker daemon system
5. Git-based memory layer
6. CLI + API hybrid orchestration layer

The system enables a user to submit tasks from desktop or mobile, and have AI agents (Claude + GPT via CLI tools) execute structured multi-step workflows:

PLAN (Claude) → IMPLEMENT (GPT) → REVIEW (Claude)

---

# 🧠 CORE PRINCIPLES

## 1. Server is the source of truth
- All AI execution happens on the Debian server
- Desktop and mobile apps are only clients
- No local AI execution on devices

## 2. Git is the memory layer
All state is stored in a local Git repository:

/ai/
  tasks/
  plans/
  implementations/
  reviews/
  context/
  logs/

Every task must be fully reconstructable from Git history.

## 3. Stateless clients
Desktop and mobile apps must not store execution state.
They only display:
- task status
- logs
- results
- diffs

---
# PROVIDER ABSTRACTION LAYER

The system MUST implement a provider-agnostic LLM interface.

All model execution must go through a provider registry.

No model names (Claude, GPT, etc.) may be hardcoded in workflow logic.

Instead, use config-based routing:

- planning → provider name from config
- implementation → provider name from config
- review → provider name from config

Each provider must implement:
- run(prompt)
- optional stream(prompt)

Providers must be swappable without modifying workflow engine.



# 🏗️ SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

## Backend (Debian Server)

Technology:
- Node.js (NestJS or Express) OR Python (FastAPI)

Responsibilities:
- Task API
- Task queue management
- Workflow orchestration
- Communication with worker daemon
- Streaming logs (WebSockets / SSE)
- Git operations interface

Endpoints:

POST /task
GET /task/:id
GET /task/:id/logs
GET /task/:id/status
GET /task/:id/artifacts
GET /task/:id/diff

---

## Worker Daemon (Always running system service)

Must run via systemd.

Responsibilities:
- Poll task queue
- Execute AI pipeline
- Manage Git operations
- Call CLI tools:
    - claude -p
    - codex or GPT CLI tool

Workflow per task:

1. Create git branch:
   ai/task/<task-id>

2. CLAUDE STEP (Planning):
   - Generate structured plan
   - Save to /ai/plans/<task-id>.md
   - Commit changes

3. GPT STEP (Implementation):
   - Read plan file
   - Modify codebase
   - Write implementation files
   - Commit changes

4. CLAUDE STEP (Review):
   - Run git diff
   - Generate review report
   - Save to /ai/reviews/<task-id>.md
   - Commit changes

5. Mark task complete

---

## Git Memory Layer

Git is mandatory for all persistence.

Rules:
- Every step must be committed
- Each task has its own branch
- No overwriting history
- All AI outputs must be stored as files

Branch structure:
main
 └── ai/task/<task-id>

